The paper proposes a novel training algorithm for reinforcement learning, which combines deep Q-learning with a constrained optimization approach to tighten optimality and encourage faster reward propagation. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed approach on the challenging Arcade Learning Environment, which involves visual recognition and control tasks, indicating that the paper may also belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions the use of neural networks, which suggests that it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
